The Herald Herald Reporter
Cabinet has this week moved its regular Tuesday sitting to Wednesday. In a statement yesterday, Chief Secretary to the President and Cabinet Dr Misheck Sibanda said the development was caused by the fact that today is a public holiday. “The Chief Secretary to the President and Cabinet, Dr Misheck J.M. Sibanda wishes to advise all Cabinet members that this week’s Cabinet meeting will be held at 0900 hours on Wednesday 26th May 2021. “This is due to the fact that Tuesday 25th May, 2021 will be a public holiday to celebrate Africa Day. Members should therefore be guided accordingly,” reads the statement